  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/6493693/" class="title-link">无限的清单：Architectonic Etcetera</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-6493693"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/2175915/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u2175915-15.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/2175915/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">Elanor Mo</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2014-01-05"
      class="main-meta">2014-01-05 10:35:53</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_6493693_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  最开始被无限的清单所吸引源于某种建筑师的内在的罗列强迫喜好症，觉得这会是一本非常有趣的书。读完之后，确实如此。除去对于罗列清单的强迫喜好症，觉得这是一本非常值得推荐给建筑师一读的书。虽然书中与空间相关的案例甚少，更多的是各种文学或是绘画中的清单的案例，但书...

